    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-23T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-23T23:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7706: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-24T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 24, 1943—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1550. From Adler to Secretary of Treasury only. TF–153. Learn confidentially
                    Chairman some 10 days ago submitted his resignation, which Dr. Kung rejected.
                    Chairman, who appears determined to quit, has again submitted resignation,
                    though agreeing to carry on until successor is appointed. While stated ground
                    for resignation is health, his actual grounds are undercurrent of friction with
                    Dr. Kung and dissatisfaction with Board’s lack of power. [Adler.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
